<br>
As for a satin sleepcap, Wal-Mart has them in their hair doodads section.  They look like showercaps, but are of satin.  You might also like a satin pillowcase, to protect your hair from tangles and breakage while you sleep.  I made mine from real satin bought at Hancock's and I love it.  (Actually, I made two, so my husband and I would match.)  I think it really makes a difference in tangles, but it took a while to get used to the feel of the satin on my face.<br>
<br>
Blessings,<br>
Carla<br>
