<br>
I'm sorry we don't have more input on this forum, but it takes a while to get a board going. <br>
<br>
My hair is VERY long, the ends reaching past my hips. It also very curly, so I don't usually need to curl it. Regency updos gave me trouble at first, since I had the same problem you do: the ends hung down my neck. Not becoming! I have several variations on Jennie's basic updo. Sometimes I do the french roll, but instead of simply pinning the roll, I clip it with a large spring-style barrette on top of my head. The ends I then arrange to cover the barrette, which provides an anchor for the hair and bobby pins.<br>
<br>
The other thing I do is gather my hair into a high ponytail. Then I wrap my hair around, like I'd do for a bun, but I leave the ends hanging out, pinning the bun where the ends are coming out. At this time, I can artfully arrange the curls to cover the bun. <br>
<br>
Keep trying and I'm sure you'll get the hang of it!<br>
<br>
